pros:
- Strong cultural values (see Leadership Principles);
- Disagreement is encouraged through cultural values;
- Possibility to grow technically or to follow a management path;
- Possibility to change teams;
- Possibility to change locations (move to another cities/countries);
- Learning resources (on-site training, online training, videos, meetups, etc.);
- Mature on-boarding process for new hires;
- Support for mental health, women and LGBT communities;

cons:
- Atmosphere may be good or bad depending on the team you're part of;
- Managers give technical guidance and sometimes enforce it;
- Managers drive scrum meetings;
- Lots of meetings without an agenda;
- Engineers don't express their opinions when they disagree;

pros:
- Great opportunities to learn new skills and advance your career;
- Top notch technology and products;
- Extremely collaborative and open culture;
- Tons of smart people around to learn and work with;
- Good benefits.
